-- Indian shares' record-setting rally continues; IT stocks jump
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Wed Sep 03, 2014 06:09AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Sept 3 (Reuters) - Indian shares hit a record high on Wednesday as software exporters such as Infosys <INFY.NS> rallied after strong U.S. manufacturing and construction data, while continued foreign buying and falling oil prices also helped.

The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> rose 0.76 percent to its fourth consecutive record high of 27,225.85, before provisionally ending 0.45 percent higher. The NSE index <.NSEI> rose as much as 0.73 percent to its third straight record high of 8,141.9. It provisionally ended up 0.39 percent.